<br>
  Overprotectiveness - there comes a point where you let your kid outside without the styrofoam padding. You let them fall and get bruised and scraped. You watch over them, and eventually you let them play without any oversight at all. It's not reasonable to expect a nuclear family to have 24 / 7 oversight of even a single child, and maintain rationality. Accidents will happen to even the most protected kid, and I think it's more important to prepare the kid for not having the buffer of parents hovering.<br>
