<br>
And it is the parent's right to determine that line.<br>
<br>
However, there is a limit. The law provides some guidlines to help those whose instincts are not sufficient. Most of us are smart enough that we never come close to those lines.<br>
<br>
Here are my lines. And because I am me, I do think less of people whose lines are significantly lower than mine. And I think people whose lines are more than slightly higher are overprotective nuts.<br>
<br>
Children can play outiside alone when they can respect the property lines and not run out into the street...when they can tell a stranger from a friend.<br>
<br>
Children must wear pads when skateboarding or biking or any similar activity...mostly to keep the hospital bills low...though I think that every child must make at least 3 trips to the emergency room by the time he is ten...just to build character. Most kids will find ways.<br>
<br>
Children do not ever sit in a car without a parent unless the parent is standing next to the car.<br>
<br>
Children under 80lbs in a car should be in safety seats of somesort. At the very least children will be in the back seat and buckled in.<br>
<br>
If your car doesn't have a back seat, and you have kids...get a car with a backseat. People who insist on driving a pickup truck without a back seat, just so they can have a truck, should not make the choice to have kids.<br>
<br>
Children should never be in an enclosed area with someone who is smoking.<br>
<br>
Children should never witness first hand anyone doing drugs or drinking to excess. They will see enough of this on TV.<br>
<br>
Children should not play with toy guns. Water shooters are available in forms other than Colt 45 and Glock immitation. Fantastic Laser pistols which in no way resemble a projectile firearm are acceptable for limited use. A child should be able to tell the difference between a toy gun and a real gun and know not to touch the real one.<br>
<br>
Play violence is fine in the form of sword(lightsaber) fights, water fights, dodgeball, wrestling.<br>
<br>
Children can be in crowded areas on their own if they know and understand how to find their way around and know where to look for help if needed.<br>
<br>
Children should not get every bit of attention they crave. Metering the attention and affection given to children is important on both sides. There should not be too much or too little, the just right window here is fairly large, though, and most parents don't miss it.<br>
<br>
Children who endanger themselves or others should be spanked.<br>
<br>
Children who make a scene in Wal-Mart do not get to go to Macdonalds afterwards, but they do not get smacked the whole way to the front of the store.<br>
<br>
Infants do not get Mountain Dew in their bottles.<br>
<br>
If your kids are malnourished and you are eating a bag of chips as you play Warcraft III on one PC and EQ on the other and smack their hand away from the bag of chips...there is a problem.<br>
<br>
If your child is crying you ARE aware of it and know why...Whether you do something about it depends on the why.<br>
<br>
Pizza is not a balanced meal. But if your kids are getting balanced meals most of the time, there is nothing wrong with occasional junk.<br>
<br>
Children will get the medical treatment they need and regular checkups...personal pride will not prevent an impoverished parent from being seen at the free clinic to tend to a child.<br>
<br>
Children do not need every toy that comes out with every new movie or TV show.<br>
<br>
Every child must at some point in his or her life have each of the following: A teddy bear, A slinky, Lincoln Logs, Legos, Monopoly, UNO, and a ball.<br>
<br>
Children should not spend every waking moment in front of a glowing screen.<br>
<br>
Parents should be aware at all times of the childs education...their abilities and whether they are in the right classes for their abilities in school. Parent should not push the kids into more advanced classes they aren't ready for nor should they allow their children to float though classes that are too easy for them. Don't trust they system to be more aware of your child than you.<br>
<br>
Parents should take the kids out for ice cream when they can and the kids deserve it.<br>
<br>
Parents should be able to speak from memory their childs full name and birthdate and eye color.<br>
<br>
Just my opinion, if its not yours, I reserve the right to attempt to convert you or flame you depending on my mood.<br>
<br>
