<br>
Stop making excuses for her actions or playing down what she did Quath, you murder lover! =P<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I don't think she is in the same league as a killer.  She is just a self centered idiot.  Even if she walked free, I doubt any parents would suddenly say, &quot;Wow!  Cool!  We can finally kill our kids.&quot;  I never made any excuses for her nor did I play down her actions.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> The punishment portion of the criminal system is not just to punish the relevant criminal it is to deter others from repeating the same crime.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
So should she get the death penality to teach other parents not to be neglectiful? Or should she have her tubes tied and child taken away and never be allowed to baby sit? Would that deter mothers from repeating her mistake?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Because at the time of their birth, they have more of a future than you. You cannot compare the contribution to society of a 6 year old vs. a 26 year old. You are thinking 2-dimensionally. Who says when they reach your age, they won't be doing more positive things than you've ever dreamed of doing? You could have the next Mother Teresa, for all you know. You bet on their life as a whole, not on their life as it is right now. It is your duty to teach, protect and provide for your children because YOU are the one that brought them into the world. It is a decision you conciously made (they may have been an &quot;accident&quot;, but you decided to keep them), please don't do it half-assed.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
They could be the next Hitler as well. All they have is potential for good or bad. What value is potential over a realized value?<br>
<br>
I think it is interesting to think which has more value: 2 year old vs 3 year old? 2 vs 10? 2 vs 18? 2 vs 26? At some age growing up, does a person become less important and less valuable? If so what is the age?<br>
<br>
I think the main reason we value children is because they are helpless and innocent and we hope for a positive future for them. But it is all emotional and not intellectual. I am not advocating anything here. I am just stirring the intellectual pot and see what people think.<br>
<br>
